(1, 3)
(-1, 4)
a^2, b^2
\dfrac{(1 + 1)^2}{a^2} + \dfrac{(3-3)^2}{b^2} = 1 \implies \dfrac 4{a^2} = 1 \implies a^2 = 4\tag{1}
\dfrac{(-1 + 1)^2}{a^2} + \dfrac{(4-3)^2}{b^2} = 1 \implies \dfrac 1{b^2} = 1 \implies b^2 = 1\tag{2}
